RDS and DynamoDB.

Deciding between RDS and DynamoDB or Relational Databases vs Non-Relational:

Relational DB:
 
	- Efficient data transfer and storage.
	- Strict Record Schema
	- Easy Querying
	- Has Query Flexibility

Non-Relational (DynamoDB):
	- No schema; Only Primary Key Restriction
	- Has Storage Flexibility
	- Limited Query Properties


To run on EC2, add AmazonRDSFullAccess and AmazonDynamoDBFullAccess to your selected role.